{"id":18738,"title":"Chromoblastomycosis: an exuberant case.","abstract":"Chromoblastomycosis is a chronic subcutaneous mycotic infection caused by dematiaceous saprophytic moulds. The most frequently isolated agent is Fonsecae pedrosoi. This article reports a case of a man from the Amazon region in Northern Brazil who presented with a lesion of 12 months' duration, which gradually increased in size until covering the majority of his right leg. A successful treatment with itraconazole was performed. ","date":"2014-04-28","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24770521","annotations":[{"name":"Brazil","weight":0.837494,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brazil"},{"name":"Chronic (medicine)","weight":0.748635,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chronic_(medicine)"},{"name":"Infection","weight":0.644384,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infection"},{"name":"Amazon Rainforest","weight":0.500666,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amazon_Rainforest"},{"name":"Itraconazole","weight":0.363235,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Itraconazole"},{"name":"Subcutaneous tissue","weight":0.322268,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Subcutaneous_tissue"},{"name":"Saprotrophic nutrition","weight":0.257569,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saprotrophic_nutrition"},{"name":"Mycosis","weight":0.238889,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mycosis"},{"name":"Lesion","weight":0.20545,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lesion"},{"name":"Leg","weight":0.0391252,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leg"},{"name":"North Region, Brazil","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_Region,_Brazil"},{"name":"Chromoblastomycosis","weight":0.0287296,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chromoblastomycosis"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.0280659,"wi